Description: Two images of Egyptian scenes and hieroglyphs within pyramid-shaped designs, both featuring a god seated in profile to right, conversing with a woman, and a third figure at far left; annotated proof. Etching, annotated in graphite
Acquisition notes: T,15.48 and 49 are listed in the 1837 inventory as an 'Etching of Egyptian Antiquities, R.Parr fec.' When the album T,15 was disbanded, the wrong numbers E,15.48 and 49 were written on the verso. Since the correct number could not be recovered (which was finally achieved in 2019) a 'U' number was added in 2006.
